  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n0.2.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge fmt\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen you set a short max line length, the formatter might wrap wide import statements to two lines, e.g.\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport { CountersUpgradeable } from\r\n    \"@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/utils/CountersUpgradeable.sol\";\r\n```\r\nif you're using a hardhat setup at the same time, its preprocessor step ([as outlined here](https://book.getfoundry.sh/config/hardhat#instructions)) cannot parse those lines correctly anymore, so hardhat can't resolve libraries anymore.\r\n\r\nI'd suggest to have another formatter option / feature that keeps lines together that being with import regardless of the line length and desired max width option.",
